🔁 General Behavior of while

The loop executes as long as the condition is true.

The condition is checked before each iteration.

✅ 1. Python

x = 0
while x < 3:
    print(x)
    x += 1


No parentheses.

No semicolons.

Indentation defines scope.

✅ 2. PHP

$x = 0;
while ($x < 3) {
    echo $x . "\n";
    $x++;
}


$ before variables.

Braces {} for block.

Semicolon ; ends statements.

✅ 3. MATLAB

x = 0;
while x < 3
    disp(x)
    x = x + 1;
end


No need for parentheses.

Ends with end.

Uses disp() for display.

✅ 4. Java

int x = 0;
while (x < 3) {
    System.out.println(x);
    x++;
}


Parentheses and braces required.

Ends with ;.

Uses System.out.println.

✅ 5. C#

int x = 0;
while (x < 3) {
    Console.WriteLine(x);
    x++;
}


Almost identical to Java.

Uses Console.WriteLine.

✅ 6. C++

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int x = 0;
while (x < 3) {
    cout << x << endl;
    x++;
}
